        <Historic_Flag>Current</Historic_Flag>
        <Parent_String>Helladic pottery styles [300107083], Aegean pottery styles [300020105], Aegean styles [300106921], Aegean [300020059], Mediterranean (Early Western World) [300020058], Early Western World [300019255], styles, periods, and cultures by region [300111079], Styles and Periods (hierarchy name) [300015646], Styles and Periods Facet [300264088]</Parent_String>
        <Hier_Rel_Type>Genus/Species-BTG</Hier_Rel_Type>
      </Preferred_Parent>
    </Parent_Relationships>
    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Refers to the style of pottery produced on the Greek mainland and dating from the Middle Helladic, characterized by simple, handmade shapes including many closed vessels, and decorated with painted geometric or linear motifs. It is also recognizable due to the dull appearance of the surface, in contrast to pottery where the surface has been burnished, and thus rendered lustrous.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Se refiere al estilo de cerámica producida en el continente griego y que data del Heládica Medio, caracterizada por simples formas hechas a mano que incluyen muchas vasijas cerradas, y decoradas con motivos lineares o geométricos pintados. Es también reconocible debido a la aburrida apariencia de la superficie, en contraste a la cerámica donde la superficie ha sido pulida y de esta manera dejada brillante.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Verwijst naar de stijl van het aardewerk dat werd vervaardigd op het Griekse vasteland vanaf de midden-Helladische tijd, en dat zich kenmerkt door de eenvoudige handgemaakte vormen waaronder veel gesloten kruiken, en door de decoratieve beschilderingen met geometrische en lineaire motieven. De stijl is ook te herkennen aan het matte uiterlijk van het oppervlak. Dit in contrast met het gepolijste en dus glanzende aardewerk.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>指稱於希臘青銅時期中期，在希臘本土製作的陶器風格，風格特徵是手工製作的簡單外形，包含了許多密閉器皿，飾以彩繪幾何或者是線性母題。此風格也以其表面缺乏光澤的外觀作為特徵，並與表面經過拋光處理而呈現光澤狀的陶器形成對比。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
